      "author": "awesome.dan (Dan)",
      "cookedHtml": "<p>Hello fellow <a href=\"http://Monday.com\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Monday.com</a> friends,</p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://Asana.com\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Asana.com</a> Month Kanban View</strong></p>\n<p></p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/2X/6/66bef5fbcba50581c03fa42fc68e8fac382247e6.jpeg\" title=\"image\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/optimized/2X/6/66bef5fbcba50581c03fa42fc68e8fac382247e6_2_690x407.jpeg\" alt=\"image\" width=\"690\" height=\"407\" /><div class=\"meta\">\n<span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">2138×1264 231 KB</span>\n</div></a></div><p></p>\n<p>You can do the following steps to make Asana month Kanban View in Monday</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Set In Progress as “Current Month”</li>\n<li>Create new statuses with subsequent months</li>\n<li>Set STUCK status as “To be planned”</li>\n<li>Switch to Kantan View</li>\n</ol>\n<p></p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/2X/c/c740eeb2551db8f6a657f11a3ac00d32c0306731.png\" title=\"image\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/optimized/2X/c/c740eeb2551db8f6a657f11a3ac00d32c0306731_2_690x256.png\" alt=\"image\" width=\"690\" height=\"256\" /><div class=\"meta\">\n<span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">1874×696 54.8 KB</span>\n</div></a></div><p></p>\n<p>Cheers <img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/apple/slight_smile.png?v=12\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" /></p>"
